Set up vim on a new machine:

1.) make symlink to vimrc:

	UNIX:
		ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc

	WINDOWS:
		In ..\Program Files\vim do
		mklink _vimrc %HOME%\.vim\.vimrc

2.) install vundle in ~/.vim
	git clone https://github.com/gmarik/vundle.git ~/.vim/bundle/vundle

3.) install plugins in vim with ":BundleInstall"

4.) done!

